'''Anne Enger''', formerly '''Anne Enger Lahnstein''' (born 9 December 1949) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] politician, but out of politics for the moment, as she is [[County governor (Norway)|County Governor]] of [[Østfold]]. A former leader of the [[Centre Party (Norway)|Centre Party]], she is best known for her opposition to the [[European Union]]. She was the front person of the successful "No to EU"-campaign at the [[Norwegian EU referendum, 1994|last membership election]] in 1994. She was also the leader in the campaign against [[Abortion in Norway|abortion on demand in Norway]] in the late 1970s.

She served as Minister of Culture 1997&ndash;2000 and for 3 weeks in 1998 she was acting Prime Minister of Norway during [[Kjell Magne Bondevik]]'s sick leave.

