Hon. '''Cynthia A. "Mother" Pratt''' (born 5 November 1945) is the former Deputy [[Prime Minister of the Bahamas]]. She attained the office when the [[Progressive Liberal Party]] came to power in the national elections of 2002.

She is a [[Protestant]] minister and served as a [[Physical Education]] teacher in the Bahamian public school system. She served as acting Prime Minister in 2005 when PM [[Perry Christie]] suffered a stroke.<ref>Norman 'Gus' Thomas. "[http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/2005/05/09/recovering.shtml Bahamas PM recovering from 'slight stroke']", Caribbean Net News, 9 May 2005. Retrieved on 2008-06-30.</ref>

She was re-elected to her seat in Parliament in the 2 May 2007 General Elections.

